    62 John's flying exists in the Platonic universe but not in the real The logical notation then is just first-order predicate calculus, where the universe of discourse is a rich set of individuals, which are real, possible and even impossible objects, events, conditions, eventualities, and so on.
    Existence and truth in the actual universe are treated as predications about individuals in the Platonic universe.
